subject: RingPlus Terms
text:
Dear tosdr,

Please review the terms for RingPlus at https://ringplus.net/legal/members/.

I had a few concerns when reading the terms. First of all, the terms, service, pricing, can change at any time for any reason, and they can change your phone's software remotely and without notice.

Second, it appears they have severe restrictions on the use of their content, and claims & restrictions on your own content.

Please see below for relevant sections.

Thanks!
Jeff


> General Rules
> 4. You cannot engage in any other behavior deemed inappropriate for > the health of the program.

> 5. You may not use your account for any commercial purpose.

> 8. RingPlus reserves the right to refuse service at any time, to > anyone, for any reason.

> General Term of Services
> “Content” includes the text, software, scripts, graphics, photos, > sounds, music, videos, audiovisual combinations, interactive features > and other materials you may view on, access through, or contribute to > the Service.
> ...
> You shall not download any Content.

> You shall be solely responsible for your own Content and the > consequences of submitting and publishing your Content on the Service. > You affirm, represent, and warrant that you own or have the necessary > licenses, rights, consents, and permissions to publish Content you > submit; and you license to RingPlus all patent, trademark, trade > secret, copyright or other proprietary rights in and to such Content > for publication on the Service pursuant to these Terms and Conditions.
> ...
> For clarity, you retain all of your ownership rights in your Content. > However, by submitting Content to RingPlus, you hereby grant RingPlus > a worldwide, non-exclusive, royalty-free, sublicenseable and > transferable license to use, reproduce, distribute, prepare derivative > works of, display, and perform the Content in connection with the > Service and RingPlus' (and its successors' and affiliates') business, > including without limitation for promoting and redistributing part or > all of the Service (and derivative works thereof) in any media formats > and through any media channels.
> ...
> You may not alter any of the hardware or software on your mobile phone > for any purpose. We may change your mobile phone’s software, > applications or programming remotely and without notice.
> ...
> The software and content on our mobile phones and devices, including > the operating system, applications, data, information, music, games, > images, text and other material, are owned by us or our business > partners

> Our Right to Make Changes
> Our service is provided at our discretion. We may change our Terms and > Conditions, including our plans and pricing, from time to time. Unless > expressly prohibited by law, we reserve the right to modify or cancel > our service or your account or take corrective action at any time and > for any reason ...

> Objectionable or Offensive Content
> You may not ... upload, download ... any Content that is ... obscene, > pornographic, ... copyrighted or otherwise objectionable ...
